## 🧠 Strategic Intelligence

### What I Confirmed from Deep Analysis

| Finding | Detail |
|---|---|
| **CI already exists** | [.github/workflows/ci.yml](file:///d:/sem4/openalgo/.github/workflows/ci.yml) runs `ruff`, builds frontend, but only tests **5 specific files** in backend |
| **Broker docstrings missing** | **1,061 functions** across 29 broker adapters have no docstrings |
| **Database docstrings missing** | **14 functions** in [database/](file:///d:/sem4/openalgo/app.py#647-679) lack docstrings |
| **Utils docstrings missing** | **30 functions** in `utils/` lack docstrings |
| **Blueprint docstrings missing** | **111 functions** in `blueprints/` lack docstrings |
| **`print()` in broker code** | 7 broker files still use bare `print()` instead of `logger` |
| **SQLite queue PR was declined** | PR based on your #949 issue was rejected — **do NOT reopen** |
| **Maintainer merges fast** | Clean, focused PRs merge in 1-2 days |
| **Kalaiviswa dominates** | Most active contributor — don't overlap with their WebSocket/adapter work |

### Hard Rules (from your strategic guidance)

> [!CAUTION]
> - ❌ Do NOT reopen the SQLite persistent queue PR  
> - ❌ Do NOT submit PRs after March 25  
