#### Day 5 (Wed) — Logging Fix: Replace `print()` in Broker Code
**Branch:** `refactor/replace-print-with-logger-brokers`  
**Tier:** 2 (comment on a new issue first!)

**Pre-step:** Open a GitHub issue:
> *Title: "refactor: replace bare print() calls with logger in 7 broker modules"*
> *Body: "Several broker adapter files still use bare `print()` instead of the project's `logger`. This loses context (timestamp, level, module name) and doesn't integrate with the Traffic Monitor. Affected files: `tradejini/mapping/order_data.py`, `tradejini/api/order_api.py`, `indmoney/mapping/transform_data.py`, `fyers/streaming/fyers_websocket_adapter.py`, `dhan_sandbox/api/order_api.py`, `firstock/api/data.py`, `dhan/api/order_api.py`. I'd like to fix these — all changes will be `logger.info()` or `logger.debug()` replacements with proper context."*

**What to do (after maintainer ACKs):**
- In each of the 7 files, replace `print(...)` with `logger.info(...)` or `logger.debug(...)`
- Add `from utils.logging import get_logger` import and `logger = get_logger(__name__)`
- Add context to log messages (which broker, which order ID where applicable)

**Lines changed:** ~100  
**Commit:** `refactor: replace bare print() with logger in broker adapters`

