#### Day 10 (Mon) — Pre-Approve: .env Permissions Fix (#960)
**Branch:** `fix/env-file-permissions`  
**Tier:** 2

**Pre-step:** Comment on [#960](https://github.com/marketcalls/openalgo/issues/960):
> *"The issue is that `chmod 600 .env` makes the file unreadable by the container's non-root user. I can fix [utils/env_check.py](file:///d:/sem4/openalgo/utils/env_check.py) to provide a clearer error message when the file exists but can't be read due to permissions, and update the install scripts to set proper ownership."*

**What to do (after ACK):**
- Update [utils/env_check.py](file:///d:/sem4/openalgo/utils/env_check.py) to catch `PermissionError` and give a specific helpful message
- Update [start.sh](file:///d:/sem4/openalgo/start.sh) to check and fix [.env](file:///d:/sem4/openalgo/.sample.env) permissions
- Update [DOCKER_README.md](file:///d:/sem4/openalgo/DOCKER_README.md) with permissions guidance

**Lines changed:** ~60  
**Commit:** `fix: handle .env permission errors gracefully in Docker (#960)`

